        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If the current millisecond precision of the Zend_Date class is set to 3 the local $max variable will evaluate to 1000,\nbut you will need to add 1001 millisecond to get it to add a whole second to the timestamp instead of 1000.\n\nInstead of the $this->_Fractional > $max condition, it should be changed to $this->_Fractional >= $max\n\nBetween lines 4420 and 4427 of Zend\/Date.php\n\n        $max = pow(10, $this->_Precision);\n        \/\/ milli includes seconds\n        if ($this->_Fractional > $max) {\n            while ($this->_Fractional > $max) {\n                $this->addSecond(1);\n                $this->_Fractional -= $max;\n            }\n        }\n\n\nshould be\n\n        $max = pow(10, $this->_Precision);\n        \/\/ milli includes seconds\n        if ($this->_Fractional >= $max) {\n            while ($this->_Fractional >= $max) {\n                $this->addSecond(1);\n                $this->_Fractional -= $max;\n            }\n        }\n"
        },
